**Some variables used in program**
**`d`** = common difference of AP
**`len`** = length of largest current AP sequence
**`( (len-2)*(len-1) )/2`** = total no of AP subsequence using this sequence

Let's say len = 5, 
then 1 sequence of length = 5
2 sequence of length = 4
3 sequence of length = 3

So total number of subsequence of using len = 1 + 2 + 3 
Or in general way = 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + ......... + (len-2) =**`( (len-2)*(len-1) )/2`**   **// Sum of first n natural numbers**
