#### 2.Single DP Array  Space:O(n) Time:O(n) (ACCEPTED)
Thanks @vesion for the [solution](https://leetcode.com/problems/arithmetic-slices/discuss/90093/3ms-C++-Standard-DP-Solution-with-Very-Detailed-Explanation).

This is a really smart approach. 
Remember this: **dp[i] represents the number of artihmatic sequences(AS) till A[i]**
So lets see how it works for `testcase :  [0,1,2,3,4]`
`dp[0] = 0`  Since not 3 numbers
`dp[1] = 0` Since not 3 numbers
`dp[2] = 0 + 1`  Since [0,1,2] is an AS
`dp[3] = dp[2] + 1` Here dp[2] provides [0,1,2] and appending [3] gives dp[2] Arithmatic Subsequences = 1. Also [1,2,3] is an AS thats why we did +1.
dp[4] = dp[3] + 1 Here dp[3] provides [0,1,2,3] and [1,2,3] and appending [4] gives dp[3] AS =  2. Also [2,3,4] is an AS thats why we did +1

Hope you get the flow of it now
