As we know, given the length of an arithmetic array, total number of arithmetic subarrays is fixed:

```
length         number_of_subArrays, with different sizes
                  3           4           5           6      ... 

3                 1
4                 2     +     1
5                 3     +     2     +     1
6                 4     +     3     +     2     +     1
...               ...
...               ...
n                 n-2   +    n-3    +     n-4        ...     = (n - 2) * (n - 1) / 2 
```
Iterate and find start/end point of each arithmetic array. then do math.
```
class Solution {
    public int numberOfArithmeticSlices(int[] nums) {
        if(nums.length < 3) return 0; 
        int len = nums.length, start = 0, diff = nums[1] - nums[0];
        int count = 0;
        for(int end = 1; end < len; ++end) {
            if(nums[end] - nums[end - 1] != diff) {
                if(end - start >= 3)
                    count += (end - start - 2) * (end - start - 1) / 2;

                start = end - 1;
                diff = nums[end] - nums[start];
            }
        }
        if(len - start >= 3)
            count += (len - start - 2) * (len - start - 1) / 2;

        return count;
    }
